        "username": "stevent",
        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/5f9b8f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-11-14T20:42:30.988Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When using the Go bindings, is there a way to prevent <a href=\"https://godoc.org/github.com/apple/foundationdb/bindings/go/src/fdb#Database.Transact\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Transact</a> from retrying when the transaction fails due to taking more than 5 seconds (<code>FoundationDB error code 1007 (Transaction is too old to perform reads or be committed)</code>? For example, this code will just keep on retrying forever:</p>\n<pre><code>\t_, err := db.Transact(func(tr fdb.Transaction) (interface{}, error) {\n\t\ttr.Get(fdb.Key(\"foo\")).MustGet()\n\n\t\t// Simulate slow transaction\n\t\ttime.Sleep(6 * time.Second)\n\n\t\ttr.Set(fdb.Key(\"bar\"), []byte{1})\n\n\t\treturn nil, nil\n\t})</code></pre>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
        "updated_at": "2019-11-14T20:42:30.988Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
        "quote_count": 0,
